post_text: We were informed today about the arrest of a District employee by the Santa Barbara Police Department. We will cooperate with law enforcement authorities as they conduct their investigation. The safety of our students always comes first, and our goal remains to protect students from any potential harm. We have no further comment on this matter until law enforcement completes their investigation.

The Board of Education passed a grading resolution, based on a Pass/Credit/Incomplete system.

During this extended closure, student grades on March 13 will be combined with improvement during Distance Learning through May 14 and an assessment of learning and participation during Distance Learning, from May 14 through June 5, to determine the final course grade.

#TeamOUHSD

I will be sending my weekly Thursday letter to parents tomorrow, which will discuss our educational plan going forward in light of today’s announcement from the Governor.

Thank You,
Dr. Penelope DeLeon

post_text:
To ensure that our students can complete school-related work and receive an education during our school closure, these locations will be distributing Chromebooks to those students who do NOT have access to a computer at home. Students participated in a Technology Survey last week, so we know exactly who needs a Chromebook at this time.

Internet Hotspots are on order for students who indicated they do not have existing internet at home. We will notify students as soon as they are available. When Hotspots arrive they can be picked up near the grab and go lunch area.

Students must have their school ID or StudentVue ID to expedite the process. Please check-in at the library during your scheduled time (we have separated times to promote social distancing). Please do not wait near other people, leave at least 6 feet between you and those around you in line.

So that we continue to practice “social distancing," Chrome Books will be distributed at:

• The PHS Library Media Center
• The RMHS Textbook room and Library
• The OHS Library
• The ACHS Library

Our OUHSD staff has been working around the clock to prepare to deliver distance learning to our students. This includes cleaning and tagging nearly 2,000 laptops and ordering hotspots to ensure that every student is able to access online learning.

We expect to extend our school closure and have a phone conference this afternoon with county officials to determine the length of extended closure. You will receive a letter explaining the details of the closure, as well as our plan for the distribution of laptops/hotspots and how to access distance learning by Wednesday this week.

Also, please know that we are in collaboration with The College Board, who has agreed to work with individual districts to postpone SAT and AP testing as needed.

http://bit.ly/schoolclosuresOUHSD

Además, sepa que estamos en colaboración con The College Board, que acordó trabajar con distritos individuales para posponer las pruebas SAT y AP según sea necesario.

Al igual que usted, a todos nos preocupa la propagación del nuevo coronavirus y la incertidumbre que está creando en nuestra vida cotidiana. Anoche, el departamento de Salud Pública del Condado de Ventura declaró una emergencia de salud local, que proporcionará recursos adicionales para la respuesta al coronavirus. Como resultado de esta declaración y en interés de la salud de nuestra comunidad, Distrito Unido de Escuelas Preparatorias de Oxnard ha decidido cerrar todas nuestras escuelas desde el lunes 16 de marzo hasta el viernes, 20 de marzo. Esperamos reabrir el lunes 23 de marzo, pero esa decisión dependerá de las circunstancias del momento. Actualizaremos a las familias sobre nuestros planes a más tardar el viernes 20 de marzo. Todas las actividades escolares se cancelan mientras nuestras escuelas están cerradas, incluyendo atletismo, presentaciones, competiciones de cualquier tipo y reuniones de padres.
http://bit.ly/schoolclosuresOUHSD

post_text:
Like you, we are all concerned about the spread of the novel coronavirus and the uncertainty it’s creating in our daily lives. Last night, the Ventura County Public Health department declared a local health emergency, which will provide additional resources for coronavirus response. As a result of this declaration and in the interest of the health of our community, Oxnard Union High School District has decided to close all of our schools beginning Monday, March 16 through Friday, March 20. We hope to reopen on Monday, March 23, but that decision will depend on the circumstances at the time. We will update families about our plans no later than Friday, March 20. All school activities are canceled while our schools are closed, including athletics, performances, competitions of any kind and parent meetings.

For more information click here: http://bit.ly/schoolclosuresOUHSD

post_text:
The entire OUHSD family are heartbroken this morning to learn of the tragic death of our beloved Hueneme High School School Resource Officer, Nathan Martin.

Officer Martin has touched the lives of countless students, staff members and families in his years at Hueneme H.S. and will be missed by all. In today’s world, we cannot underestimate the importance of our SRO’s who not only protect our students and staff every day, but provide the mentorship and counsel at the forefront of our efforts to ensure our students thrive.

Our thoughts, prayers and condolences go to the Martin family, the Oxnard Police Department and our Viking familia as they try to work through this devastating loss.

post_text:
Possible Power Outages: Dear OUHSD Families,

We have been notified that some of our schools in the incorporated and unincorporated areas of Camarillo (Adolfo Camarillo HS, Frontier HS, Rancho Campana HS and Rio Mesa HS) may be affected by planned power outages. At this time, there are no planned outages for the Oxnard or Hueneme areas. In the event of a power outage, schools will remain open. Should a power outage occur over night, school will be open the following day.

In service,

Penelope DeLeon, Ed.D.

Superintendent, Oxnard Union High School District
